<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="534" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/4564: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Personal Representative of the
                                    President</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-28T18:00:00-05:00">December 28, 1933—6
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>532. Uruguayan Minister tells me he is making another attempt to have
                                his conciliation plan accepted. I told him I wished him every
                                success. He will see me tonight to report developments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>